f play and the importance of allowing children more time and space for it. The book throws down a challenge to both play advocates and governments, to make effective policy that respects, protects and fulfils children’s right to play as a priority. It is an essential tool for practitioners and campaigners around the world.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aChild developmentvCase studiesxGovernment policy. 0aChild welfarevCase studiesxGovernment policy. 0aChildren's rights. 0aPlayvCase studiesxGovernment policy. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Children's Studies.2bisacsh1 aHart, Roger, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBristol University Press Complete eBook-Package 2015z97831111964280 cprintz978144731942940uhttps://doi.org/10.56687/9781447319436?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781447319436423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781447319436/original  a978-3-11-119642-8  Bristol University Press Complete eBook-Package 2015b2015  aGBV-deGruyter-alles